     OOOOOOOOPPPPSSSS((((UUUU1111))))             LLLLSSSS----DDDDOOOOSSSS 6666 ---- UUUUttttiiiilllliiiittttiiiieeeessss 1111              OOOOOOOOPPPPSSSS((((UUUU1111))))



          <<<<....>>>>  Allows one or both digits of the repeat value to be
               erased.  This can be done until an eeeeddddiiiitttt command is
               entered.  The last digit entered (the ones' digit) is
               the first to be deleted.

          <<<<UUUU>>>>  Aborts all changes made so far and restores the line to
               its original state.  The cursor is positioned to the
               first column.


          Insert commands:

          <<<<IIII>>>>  Enters iiiinnnnsssseeeerrrrtttt mode.  Characters will be inserted in
               front of the character that is under the cursor.
               Pressing <<<<EEEENNNNTTTTEEEERRRR>>>> submits the command to the operating
               system.  Pressing <<<<FFFF3333>>>>, <<<<BBBBRRRREEEEAAAAKKKK>>>>, <<<<SSSSHHHHIIIIFFFFTTTT>>>><<<<UUUUPPPP----AAAARRRRRRRROOOOWWWW>>>> or
               any other control character exits iiiinnnnsssseeeerrrrtttt mode.

          <<<<XXXX>>>>  Enters iiiinnnnsssseeeerrrrtttt mode, but first the cursor is moved to
               the end of the line.  See the <<<<IIII>>>> for information on
               iiiinnnnsssseeeerrrrtttt mode.

          <<<<HHHH>>>> or <<<<TTTT>>>>
               Deletes all characters to the right of the cursor and
               enters iiiinnnnsssseeeerrrrtttt mode.  See the <<<<IIII>>>> command.


          Editing commands:

          [_n]<<<<CCCC>>>>
               Changes the character under the cursor to the next
               character that is typed.  After the change the cursor
               moves one position to the right.  Pressing <<<<BBBBRRRREEEEAAAAKKKK>>>> or
               <<<<FFFF3333>>>> will exit the cccchhhhaaaannnnggggeeee mode.

          [_n]<<<<DDDD>>>>
               Deletes the character under the cursor and moves the
               text on the right of the cursor to the left to fill the
               hole.


          Searching commands:

          [_n]<<<<SSSS>>>>
               _O_o_p_s reads the next character that is typed and
               searches for that character on the current line.  If a
               match is found, the cursor to that position.  If the
               character that is entered is not found to the right of
               the cursor, the cursor is moved to the end of the line.
               The search is case-sensitive; in other words, if you
               search for the letter 't', the uppercase letter 'T'
               will not be found by the search.



